\\n## 7. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go`\\n\\n### `RepoRoot() (string, error)` (line 61-93)\\n```go\\nvar (\\n\\trepoRootMu       sync.RWMutex\\n\\trepoRootCache    string\\n\\trepoRootCacheDir string\\n)\\n\\nfunc RepoRoot() (string, error) {\\n\\tcwd, err := os.Getwd()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\tcwd = \\\"\\\"\\n\\t}\\n\\trepoRootMu.RLock()\\n\\tif repoRootCache != \\\"\\\" && repoRootCacheDir == cwd {\\n\\t\\tcached := repoRootCache\\n\\t\\trepoRootMu.RUnlock()\\n\\t\\treturn cached, nil\\n\\t}\\n\\trepoRootMu.RUnlock()\\n\\t// Cache miss\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"git\\\", \\\"rev-parse\\\", \\\"--show-toplevel\\\")\\n\\toutput, err := cmd.Output()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\", fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to get git repository root: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\troot := strings.TrimSpace(string(output))\\n\\trepoRootMu.Lock()\\n\\trepoRootCache = root\\n\\trepoRootCacheDir = cwd\\n\\trepoRootMu.Unlock()\\n\\treturn root, nil\\n}\\n```\\n**Has RWMutex caching** keyed by CWD. First call spawns a subprocess, subsequent calls from the same CWD return from cache. `ClearRepoRootCache()` (line 97-102) resets it.\\n\\n**Key contrast**: `strategy.GetWorktreePath()` does the exact same `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` but has **no caching**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/mise.toml`\\n\\nKey task definitions:\\n```toml\\n[tasks.test]\\nrun = \\\"go test ./...\\\"\\n\\n[tasks.\\\"test:integration\\\"]\\nrun = \\\"go test -tags=integration ./cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/...\\\"\\n\\n[tasks.\\\"test:ci\\\"]\\nrun = \\\"go test -tags=integration -race ./...\\\"\\n\\n[tasks.bench]\\nrun = \\\"go test -bench=. -benchmem -run='^$' -timeout=10m ./...\\\"\\n\\n[tasks.\\\"bench:cpu\\\"]\\nrun = \\\"\\\"\\\"PKG=\\\"${BENCH_PKG:-./cmd/entire/cli/benchutil/}\\\"\\ngo test -bench=. -benchmem -run='^$' -cpuprofile=cpu.prof -timeout=10m \\\"$PKG\\\" \\\"\\\"\\