ms strategy-specific cleanup at the end of a turn.\\n   463→\\t// Work items are read from state (e.g. TurnCheckpointIDs), not from the\\n   464→\\t// action list. The state has already been updated by ApplyTransition;\\n   465→\\t// the caller saves it after this method returns.\\n   466→\\tHandleTurnEnd(state *session.State) error\\n   467→}\\n   468→\\n   469→// RestoredSession describes a single session that was restored by RestoreLogsOnly.\\n   470→// Each session may come from a different agent, so callers use this to print\\n   471→// per-session resume commands without re-reading the metadata tree.\\n   472→type RestoredSession struct {\\n   473→\\tSessionID string\\n   474→\\tAgent     agent.AgentType\\n   475→\\tPrompt    string\\n   476→}\\n   477→\\n   478→// LogsOnlyRestorer is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   479→// restoring session logs without file state restoration.\\n   480→// This is used for \\\"logs-only\\\" rewind points where only the session transcript\\n   481→// can be restored (file state requires git checkout).\\n   482→type LogsOnlyRestorer interface {\\n   483→\\t// RestoreLogsOnly restores session logs from a logs-only rewind point.\\n   484→\\t// Does not modify the working directory - only restores the transcript\\n   485→\\t// to the agent's session directory (determined per-session from checkpoint metadata).\\n   486→\\t// If force is false, prompts for confirmation when local logs have newer timestamps.\\n   487→\\t// Returns info about each restored session so callers can print correct resume commands.\\n   488→\\tRestoreLogsOnly(point RewindPoint, force bool) ([]RestoredSession, error)\\n   489→}\\n   490→\\n   491→// SessionResetter is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   492→// resetting session state and shadow branches.\\n   493→// This is used by the \\\"reset\\\" command to clean up shadow branches\\n   494→// and session state when a user wants to start fresh.\\n   495→type Session