7d-9d52-3dea4e57494f\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"84c3f58e-c9ce-45a5-a682-3736d6322c74\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"239c414d-2b2a-42d8-b557-85f3197d1015\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"enable_performance_optimzations\",\"slug\":\"woolly-toasting-corbato\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TwFXhrSBeuMGM6vmcBbxfN\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a thorough understanding of the full execution path. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Full Execution Path: Claude Code Hooks (Session Start and Stop)\\n\\n### 1. Hook Installation (`InstallHooks`)\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks.go` (lines 46-225)\\n\\nThe `ClaudeCodeAgent.InstallHooks()` method writes entries into `.claude/settings.json` at the repo root. In production mode, the following hook commands are installed:\\n\\n| Claude Code Event     | Command Installed                                          | Matcher  |\\n|-----------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|----------|\\n| `SessionStart`        | `entire hooks claude-code session-start`                  | (none)   |\\n| `SessionEnd`          | `entire hooks claude-code session-end`                    | (none)   |\\n| `Stop`                | `entire hooks claude-code stop`                           | (none)   |\\n| `UserPromptSubmit`    | `entire hooks claude-code user-prompt-submit`             | (none)   |\\n| `PreToolUse`          | `entire hooks claude-code pre-task`                       | `Task`   |\\n| `PostToolUse`         | `entire hooks claude-code post-task`                      | `Task`   |\\n| `PostToolUse`         | `entire hooks claude-code post-todo`                      | `TodoWrite` |\\n\\nIt also installs a `permissions.deny` rule: `Read(./.entire/metadata/**)` to block Claude from reading session metadata.\\n\\nIn local-dev mode, the commands use `go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code ...` instead.\\n\\nThe JSON structure stored is an array of `ClaudeHookMatcher` objects, each with an optional `matcher` string (tool name for PreToolUse/PostToolUse) and an array of `hooks` entries (type: \\\"command\\\", command: the string above).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Hook Command Registration\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` (lines 13-35)\\n\\n`newHooksCmd()` creates the `entire hooks` command, then dynamically adds subcommands for each registered agent (claude-code, gemini, opencode). For each agent, it calls `newAgentHooksCmd()`.\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` (lines 47-71)\\n\\n`newAgentHooksCmd()` creates the `entire hooks claude-code` subcommand with:\\n- `PersistentPreRunE`: calls `initHookLogging()` which sets up the log-level getter and initializes file-based logging\\n- `PersistentPostRunE`: calls `logging.Close()` to flush logs\\n- For each hook name returned by `agent.HookNames()` (session-start, session-end, stop, user-prompt-submit, pre-task, post-task, post-todo), adds a subcommand via `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()`.\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` (lines 91-160)\\n\\n`newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()` creates the actual leaf command (e.g., `entire hooks claude-code stop`). Its `RunE` function is the entry point for every hook invocation:\\n\\n1. **Skip if not in a git repo**: `paths.RepoRoot()` check -- returns nil (no error) if not in git repo\\n2. **Skip if Entire not enabled**: `IsEnabled()` loads `.entire/settings.json` and checks `Enabled` field\\n3. **Timing**: Captures start time\\n4. **Logging context**: Creates context with agent name and component \\\"hooks\\\"\\n5. **Get strategy name**: `GetStrategy()` loads settings, resolves strategy (defaults to manual-commit)\\n6. **Set current hook agent**: Sets `currentHookAgentName` package variable so downstream code can identify the agent\\n7. **Parse hook event**: Calls `ag.ParseHookEvent(hookName, cmd.InOrStdin())` to parse JSON from stdin into a normalized `agent.Event`\\n8. **Dispatch**:\\n   - If event is non-nil: calls `DispatchLifecycleEvent(ag, event)`\\n   - Special case: if Claude Code + PostTodo: calls `handleClaudeCodePostTodo()` directly\\n   - Otherwise: no-op (pass-through hook)\\n9. **Log duration**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. `UserPromptSubmit` Hook (Turn Start / Session Start)\\n\\n**Hook script runs**: `entire hooks claude-code user-prompt-submit`\\n\\n**Claude Code sends on stdin** (parsed by `parseTurnStart` in lifecycle.go):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/.jsonl\\\",\\n  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user's prompt text\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 155-167)\\n\\n`ParseHookEvent(\\\"user-prompt-submit\\\", stdin)` calls `parseTurnStart()` which:\\n- Reads stdin JSON into `userPromptSubmitRaw` struct\\n- Returns `agent.Event{Type: agent.TurnStart, SessionID, SessionRef (transcript path), Prompt, Timestamp}`\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` (lines 112-148)\\n\\n`handleLifecycleTurnStart(ag, event)` does the following:\\n\\n#### Step 3a: Validate\\n- Logs \\\"turn-start\\\" at INFO level\\n- Validates `event.SessionID` is non-empty and passes `validation.ValidateSessionID()`\\n\\n#### Step 3b: Capture Pre-Prompt State\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/state.go` (lines 92-146)\\n\\n`CapturePrePromptState(ag, sessionID, sessionRef)`:\\n1. Creates `.entire/tmp/` directory (via `paths.AbsPath(paths.EntireTmpDir)`)\\n2. **Git status scan**: `getUntrackedFilesForState()` opens the git repo with go-git, calls `worktree.Status()`, collects all untracked files (excluding `.entire/` directory)\\n3. **Transcript position**: If agent implements `TranscriptAnalyzer` (Claude Code does), calls `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition(sessionRef)` which counts lines in the JSONL transcript file\\n4. **Writes state file**: Saves `PrePromptState{SessionID, Timestamp, UntrackedFiles, TranscriptOffset}` to `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<sessionID>.json`\\n\\n#### Step 3c: Strategy EnsureSetup\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go` (lines 98-120)\\n\\n`strat.EnsureSetup()` (ManualCommitStrategy):\\n1. **Gitignore**: `EnsureEntireGitignore()` -- ensures `.entire/` is in `.gitignore`\\n2. **Metadata branch**: Opens git repo, calls `EnsureMetadataBranch(repo)` to ensure the orphan `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch exists\\n3. **Git hooks**: Checks if git hooks are installed (`IsGitHookInstalled()`), if not calls `InstallGitHook(true)` which installs prepare-commit-msg, commit-msg, post-commit, and pre-push hooks that delegate to `entire hooks git ...`\\n\\n#### Step 3d: Initialize Session (SessionInitializer)\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (lines 1397-1486)\\n\\n`initializer.InitializeSession(sessionID, agentType, sessionRef, prompt)` (ManualCommitStrategy):\\n\\n**Case 1: Existing session (state found with BaseCommit set)**\\n1. Loads session state from `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionID>.json`\\n2. Fires `session.EventTurnStart` transition on the state machine (IDLE -> ACTIVE, or ACTIVE -> ACTIVE for Ctrl-C recovery)\\n3. Generates a new `TurnID` (random 12-hex ID)\\n4. Backfills `AgentType` and `FirstPrompt` if empty\\n5. Updates `TranscriptPath` if changed\\n6. Clears `LastCheckpointID` and `TurnCheckpointIDs` (fresh turn)\\n7. **Calculates prompt attribution**: `calculatePromptAttributionAtStart()` -- reads the shadow branch tip tree (last checkpoint), base commit tree, and current worktree status to compute line-level attribution (user vs agent changes). Stores in `state.PendingPromptAttribution`\\n8. **Shadow branch migration**: `migrateShadowBranchIfNeeded()` -- if HEAD moved (pull/rebase), renames shadow branch from `entire/<old-hash>-<worktreeHash>` to `entire/<new-hash>-<worktreeHash>`\\n9. Saves updated session state\\n\\n**Case 2: New session (no state or empty BaseCommit)**\\n1. Calls private `initializeSession()`:\\n\\n   **File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go` (lines 195-249)\\n   \\n   - Gets HEAD hash from git\\n   - Gets worktree path and worktree ID (for multi-worktree support)\\n   - Collects untracked files (for rewind preservation)\\n   - Generates a `TurnID`\\n   - Creates `SessionState` with: SessionID, CLIVersion, BaseCommit (HEAD hash), WorktreePath, WorktreeID, StartedAt, TurnID, StepCount=0, UntrackedFilesAtStart, AgentType, TranscriptPath, FirstPrompt\\n   - Saves to `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionID>.json`\\n2. Fires `session.EventTurnStart` transition (IDLE -> ACTIVE)\\n3. Calculates prompt attribution\\n4. Saves state\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `SessionStart` Hook\\n\\n**Hook script runs**: `entire hooks claude-code session-start`\\n\\n**Claude Code sends on stdin** (parsed by `parseSessionStart` in lifecycle.go):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/.jsonl\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 142-153)\\n\\n`ParseHookEvent(\\\"session-start\\\", stdin)` calls `parseSessionStart()` which returns `agent.Event{Type: agent.SessionStart, SessionID, SessionRef, Timestamp}`.\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` (lines 61-108)\\n\\n`handleLifecycleSessionStart(ag, event)`:\\n\\n1. **Validates** session_id is present and valid\\n2. **Builds banner message**: `\\\"\\\\n\\\\nPowered by Entire:\\\\n  This conversation will be linked to your next commit.\\\"`\\n3. **Concurrent session check**: If strategy implements `ConcurrentSessionChecker`, calls `CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints(sessionID)` to count other active sessions on same base commit. If >0, appends count to the message.\\n4. **Outputs JSON response to stdout**: `outputHookResponse(message)` which writes `{\\\"systemMessage\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` -- Claude Code displays this as a system message to the user\\n5. **State machine transition**: Loads session state for this session ID. If state exists, fires `session.EventSessionStart` transition (which may clear EndedAt if session was previously ended). Saves the state.\\n\\nNote: SessionStart fires before UserPromptSubmit. SessionStart shows the banner; UserPromptSubmit does the heavy initialization (state capture, strategy setup, session init).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `Stop` Hook (Turn End)\\n\\n**Hook script runs**: `entire hooks claude-code stop`\\n\\n**Claude Code sends on stdin**:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/.jsonl\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 169-179)\\n\\n`ParseHookEvent(\\\"stop\\\", stdin)` calls `parseTurnEnd()` which returns `agent.Event{Type: agent.TurnEnd, SessionID, SessionRef, Timestamp}`.\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` (lines 154-424)\\n\\n`handleLifecycleTurnEnd(ag, event)` -- this is the most complex handler. Full call chain:\\n\\n#### Step 5a: Validation\\n- Validates transcript file exists\\n- **Empty repo check**: Opens repository, checks `IsEmptyRepository()` -- if no commits yet, prints \\\"skipping checkpoint\\\" and returns\\n\\n#### Step 5b: Metadata Directory Creation\\n- Creates `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/` directory\\n\\n#### Step 5c: Transcript Preparation\\n- If agent implements `TranscriptPreparer` (Claude Code does), calls `PrepareTranscript(transcriptRef)`:\\n\\n  **File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 126-129, 237-312)\\n  \\n  `waitForTranscriptFlush(sessionRef, time.Now())`: Polls the transcript file (up to 3 seconds, every 50ms) looking for a `hook_progress` sentinel entry containing `\\\"hooks claude-code stop\\\"` with a recent timestamp. This ensures Claude Code's async transcript writer has flushed all pending writes before we read it.\\n\\n#### Step 5d: Copy Transcript\\n- `ag.ReadTranscript(transcriptRef)` reads the JSONL file\\n- Writes to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/full.jsonl`\\n\\n#### Step 5e: Copy Export JSON (OpenCode only)\\n- If `<transcriptRef>.export.json` exists, copies it too\\n\\n#### Step 5f: Load Pre-Prompt State\\n- `LoadPrePromptState(sessionID)` reads `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<sessionID>.json`\\n- Uses the `TranscriptOffset` from that state\\n\\n#### Step 5g: Extract Metadata via Agent Interfaces\\nUsing `TranscriptAnalyzer` and `SubagentAwareExtractor`:\\n1. **Prompts**: `analyzer.ExtractPrompts(transcriptRef, transcriptOffset)` -- parses JSONL from the offset, extracts user messages\\n2. **Summary**: `analyzer.ExtractSummary(transcriptRef)` -- finds last assistant text block\\n3. **Modified files**: `subagentExtractor.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptRef, transcriptOffset, subagentsDir)` -- extracts files from Write/Edit tool uses in both main agent and subagent transcripts\\n4. **Transcript position**: Gets current line count\\n\\n#### Step 5h: Write Metadata Files\\n- Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` (all prompts joined with `---`)\\n- Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt`\\n- Generates commit message from last prompt\\n\\n#### Step 5i: Detect File Changes\\n- Gets repo root via `paths.RepoRoot()`\\n- **Git status via go-git**: `DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)` opens repo, gets worktree status, categorizes files into Modified, New (untracked minus pre-existing), Deleted\\n- **Filters paths**: `FilterAndNormalizePaths()` converts absolute to relative, excludes `.entire/` paths\\n- **Filters committed files**: `filterToUncommittedFiles()` compares working tree content with HEAD to exclude files already committed mid-turn\\n- If zero total changes: transitions session phase, cleans up pre-prompt state, returns (no checkpoint)\\n\\n#### Step 5j: Create Context File\\n- Writes `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md` with session info, prompts, and summary\\n\\n#### Step 5k: Get Git Author\\n- `GetGitAuthor()` reads from git config\\n\\n#### Step 5l: Calculate Token Usage\\n- If agent implements `SubagentAwareExtractor`: `CalculateTotalTokenUsage(transcriptRef, transcriptLinesAtStart, subagentsDir)` -- sums up input/output/cache tokens from all API responses in the transcript (including subagent transcripts)\\n\\n#### Step 5m: Save Step (Strategy)\\n**File:** `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` (lines 24-120+)\\n\\n`strat.SaveStep(ctx)` (ManualCommitStrategy):\\n1. Opens git repository\\n2. Loads session state; initializes if needed\\n3. Checks for HEAD migration (`migrateAndPersistIfNeeded`)\\n4. Gets checkpoint store\\n5. Uses pending prompt attribution from InitializeSession\\n6. Calls `store.WriteTemporary()` which:\\n   - Builds an in-memory git tree containing all modified/new files + metadata directory\\n   - Creates a commit on the shadow branch `entire/<HEAD-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` with trailers (Entire-Session, Entire-Metadata, Entire-Strategy)\\n   - Deduplication: if tree hash matches previous commit, skips\\n7. Updates session state: increments StepCount, updates transcript position\\n8. Saves session state to `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionID>.json`\\n\\n#### Step 5n: Session Phase Transition and Cleanup\\n- **Auto-commit transcript position update**: 